The paper deals with an online optimization problem with matroid constraints and submodular objective functions, which are topics commonly studied in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the competitive analysis of deterministic and randomized algorithms for this problem, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and online algorithms (cs.DS). The use of submodular functions and matroid constraints also suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
